Algorithm description: The new algorithm calculates the scores for each bin by taking the inverse of the square of the difference between the bin capacity and the item size, then normalizing the scores by dividing them by the maximum score across all bins.

Code:

import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    # Calculate the scores for the bins
    square_difference = np.square(bins - item)
    scores = 1 / square_difference
    
    max_score = np.max(scores)
    scores = scores / max_score  # Normalize the scores by dividing by the maximum score
    
    return scores
